# Entity handler

Two-argument handler — `(Request, Map[String, Any]) => Response`.
The `ctx` map is supplied by `mount()` and distinguishes which collection to serve.

```scala
(req, ctx) => {
  val coll = ctx("coll").toString
  val id   = req.params("id")
  Response.json(s"""{"collection":"$coll","id":"$id"}""")
}
```
